10 AS INTRODUCED
11 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; creating
depreciation schedule for farm equipment and farm
12 tractors for purposes of ad valorem taxation;
defining terms; requiring the fair cash value to
13 depreciate by certain percentage each year;
prescribing amount of depreciation; providing
14 presumption of fair cash value; requiring the
Oklahoma Tax Commission to promulgate rules and forms
15 as may be necessary; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2817.4 of Title 68, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. As used in this act:
24
HB3178 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. "Farm equipment" means any farm tractor, utility task
2 vehicle (UTV), or vehicle that does not meet the definition in
3 Section 2809 of this title so long as it is used in agricultural
4 production on a farm or ranch that is owned, leased, or operated by
5 the owner of such equipment. This definition shall also include any
6 other personal property as defined by Section 2807 of this title so
7 long as it is used in agricultural production on a farm or ranch
8 that is owned, leased, or operated by the owner of such equipment;
9 and
10 2. "Farm tractor" means farm tractors as defined by Section
11 2809 of this title.
12 B. For purposes of determining the fair cash value of farm
13 equipment and farm tractors for ad valorem taxation, the county
14 assessor shall apply the following depreciation schedule:
15 1. The fair cash value of farm equipment and farm tractors
16 shall be determined as of January 1 of each year by applying a
17 deprecation factor of twenty-five percent (25%) per tax year to the
18 original cost of the farm equipment or farm tractor, beginning with
19 the first tax year in which the farm equipment and farm tractor is
20 subject to ad valorem taxation;
21 2. The depreciated fair cash value of farm equipment and farm
22 tractors shall be calculated by multiplying the original cost of the
23 farm equipment or farm tractor by the cumulative depreciation factor
24 of the applicable year of the schedule, as follows:
HB3178 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 a. for the first tax year, seventy-five percent (75%) of
2 the original cost,
3 b. for the second tax year, fifty percent (50%) of the
4 original cost,
5 c. for the third tax year, twenty-five percent (25%) of
6 the original cost, and
7 d. for the fourth tax year and all subsequent tax years,
8 zero percent (0%) of the original cost;
9 3. The amount determined pursuant to this subsection shall be
10 presumed to be the fair cash value of farm equipment and farm
11 tractors for purposes of ad valorem taxation unless expressly
12 authorized by the Oklahoma Constitution or Oklahoma Statutes.
13 C. The Oklahoma Tax Commission shall promulgate rules and forms
14 as may be necessary to implement and administer the provisions of
15 this act.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective January 1, 2027.
17
